WEBVTT

00:01.040 --> 00:02.840
ROZ: I changed my plans, Michael.

00:03.600 --> 00:04.840
Worried you might intervene.

00:05.200 --> 00:06.920
-How is she?
-Not good.

00:07.000 --> 00:08.520
She won't tell you that,
but she's not good.

00:09.120 --> 00:10.240
I'm scared there's no heaven.

00:10.440 --> 00:12.200
Death is just the end.

00:12.280 --> 00:13.760
And I'm scared of that end.

00:13.840 --> 00:15.840
So, how is the flashbacks going?

00:15.920 --> 00:17.280
Flash forwards these days.

00:17.640 --> 00:19.880
It's purgatory,
people telling each other bitter truths.

00:20.040 --> 00:22.880
You made me a self-loathing wreck.

00:23.040 --> 00:24.080
And the phone rang.

00:24.520 --> 00:26.960
Helen Oyenusi about Vernon.

00:27.160 --> 00:28.200
I didn't pick up.

00:28.280 --> 00:30.080
Few hours later, he was dead.

00:30.160 --> 00:31.560
They won't let me see him.

00:31.760 --> 00:34.960
MICHAEL: Some police officers
in my parish have killed a young man.

00:35.040 --> 00:38.000
They are all colluding,
protecting the officers responsible.

00:38.400 --> 00:39.840
I'd like to bury my son.

00:53.800 --> 00:57.680
♪ Broken windows and empty hallways

00:58.200 --> 01:02.800
♪ A pale, dead moon in the sky
streaked with grey

01:04.640 --> 01:09.600
♪ Human kindness is overflowing

01:09.680 --> 01:15.720
♪ And I think it's going to rain today ♪

01:26.640 --> 01:30.520
MICHAEL: I'm going to sprinkle
Roz's coffin with holy water now.

01:30.600 --> 01:32.520
To remind us of her baptism.

01:36.400 --> 01:40.320
"Jesus said to her:
I am the resurrection and the life.

01:41.120 --> 01:43.600
"Whoever believes in me
shall live even in death.

01:44.560 --> 01:48.000
"And whoever lives and believes in me
shall never die."

01:51.760 --> 01:54.360
Eternal rest grant unto her, O lord.

01:55.080 --> 01:57.800
And let perpetual light shine upon her.

01:58.240 --> 01:59.880
May she rest in peace.

02:00.120 --> 02:01.240
Amen.

02:01.640 --> 02:04.640
May her soul and the souls
of all the faithful departed,

02:05.800 --> 02:08.520
through the mercy of God, rest in peace.

02:08.960 --> 02:10.080
Amen.

02:10.720 --> 02:11.840
[SOBBING]

02:16.440 --> 02:18.040
[SNIFFLING]

02:46.080 --> 02:47.560
May I scrounge a lift from you?

02:48.400 --> 02:49.480
Yes.

02:53.240 --> 02:54.760
She was never religious.

02:56.280 --> 02:57.320
No?

02:58.160 --> 02:59.840
-No.
-[CHUCKLES]

03:01.840 --> 03:03.080
So, how did you meet?

03:04.240 --> 03:05.560
She came to see me.

03:06.800 --> 03:08.880
To tell you what she decided to do?

03:11.480 --> 03:13.160
I can't tell you that, Chloe.

03:15.880 --> 03:17.360
Did she talk about us?

03:17.920 --> 03:19.000
Oh, yes.

03:20.000 --> 03:22.920
She said she loved you very much.
You and the boys.

03:24.080 --> 03:25.760
It didn't stop her though, did it?

03:27.120 --> 03:29.360
-Didn't her letter explain it all?
-No.

03:31.080 --> 03:33.600
That was all about
how much she loved us.

03:38.440 --> 03:41.040
Do you think she wanted you
to talk her out of it?

03:43.200 --> 03:44.240
Perhaps.

03:45.240 --> 03:46.640
Did you try?

03:48.960 --> 03:50.720
Yes, I tried very hard.

03:54.240 --> 03:55.760
I'm gonna pay it all back.

03:56.800 --> 03:58.840
Oh, no-one expects that of you.

03:58.920 --> 04:00.400
I expect it of me.

04:02.080 --> 04:04.560
It'll take me years,
but I'm gonna pay it all back.

04:06.000 --> 04:07.120
Every penny.

04:13.320 --> 04:14.360
[CAR DOOR SHUTS]

04:16.920 --> 04:18.480
Thanks very much.

04:18.960 --> 04:20.280
I appreciate it.

04:20.440 --> 04:21.560
Hiya.

04:22.360 --> 04:23.920
[INDISTINCT CHATTERING]

04:31.360 --> 04:33.760
Chloe says she's gonna pay it all back.

04:34.200 --> 04:35.240
[SIGHS]

04:36.680 --> 04:38.200
Do you know how much?

04:38.640 --> 04:42.000
Yeah, just over 230,000,
I think she said.

04:42.080 --> 04:43.320
-Yeah.
-[EXHALES]

04:46.280 --> 04:49.440
The night she told me, I couldn't sleep.

04:51.160 --> 04:52.440
I was so angry.

04:53.840 --> 04:57.880
And now if you pay me it back,
I'd burn it.

05:00.880 --> 05:02.160
She lost it all on the machines?

05:02.960 --> 05:04.040
Yeah.

05:04.760 --> 05:06.080
Well, that helps.

05:07.400 --> 05:09.840
I thought she robbed me
because she could.

05:10.880 --> 05:14.080
-But she did it because she had to.
-Yeah. She did.

05:16.720 --> 05:18.600
They're all in a pension scheme at work.

05:19.680 --> 05:21.360
Lump sum on death.

05:22.040 --> 05:23.960
And death in service pays double.

05:25.120 --> 05:26.400
[SCOFFS]

05:26.480 --> 05:28.040
Oh, the irony, Father.

05:29.800 --> 05:34.120
In life, she lost it all,
in death, she hit the jackpot.

05:38.440 --> 05:40.480
You don't need to
reproach yourself about it.

05:40.600 --> 05:42.120
You wanna bet?

05:43.120 --> 05:44.520
No pun intended.

05:45.880 --> 05:48.520
I told her I was phoning the police.
That's what did it.

05:48.600 --> 05:51.880
Look, she'd resolved to kill herself
weeks before.

05:52.160 --> 05:54.240
It was the shame that did it.

05:55.400 --> 05:58.800
What you said,
it didn't make any difference.

06:01.080 --> 06:02.560
I wanna believe that so much.

06:02.680 --> 06:03.920
Oh, it's the truth.

06:05.240 --> 06:06.560
It's the truth.

06:10.080 --> 06:11.280
Thank you.

06:15.880 --> 06:17.480
Yeah, take care.

06:29.800 --> 06:31.120
DANIEL: It's cold.

06:31.440 --> 06:33.480
Right. Let's see if she's in.

06:34.400 --> 06:35.640
You all right?

06:39.800 --> 06:43.680
Hey, love, I'm sorry to bother you...

06:43.760 --> 06:45.240
Are you a friend of Helen's?

06:45.480 --> 06:46.680
I'm her brother.

06:46.760 --> 06:48.520
Oh, lovely to meet you.

06:49.120 --> 06:51.600
I'm Carl, I live just across the road.

06:55.920 --> 06:57.600
I'm so sorry for your loss.

07:01.000 --> 07:02.200
Have you come far?

07:02.760 --> 07:04.040
Trinidad.

07:04.280 --> 07:05.600
Well, I won't keep you.

07:05.760 --> 07:08.000
Would you mind passing these
onto Helen for me?

07:08.760 --> 07:10.400
Tell her I've been meaning
to call over for ages

07:10.480 --> 07:13.400
but I didn't like to intrude.

07:14.520 --> 07:15.560
[CHILD SNICKERING]

07:15.640 --> 07:17.760
You can't get
anything like these around here.

07:18.560 --> 07:20.680
I had to go
all the way into town to get them.

07:21.320 --> 07:25.560
Gladioli, flamboyant
rather than garish, I feel.

07:27.880 --> 07:30.480
Boys, take your luggage
and go and stand by the door.

07:30.600 --> 07:31.680
CHILDREN: Why?

07:32.520 --> 07:34.720
Boys, luggage.

07:36.400 --> 07:37.920
I hope she likes them.

07:40.520 --> 07:42.520
You can leave them there with the rest.

07:44.960 --> 07:46.480
Well, I... I was hoping, perhaps,

07:46.560 --> 07:48.280
-that you could...
-There, is fine.

07:54.520 --> 07:56.880
Maybe I'll just leave it for now, then.

08:06.680 --> 08:09.680
-Are you well, Michael?
-Me? Yeah.

08:11.240 --> 08:15.240
You seemed troubled at mass.

08:15.520 --> 08:16.760
Helen!

08:18.800 --> 08:19.840
Oh!

08:22.240 --> 08:23.280
[SHRIEKS]

08:25.640 --> 08:26.680
Oh!

08:30.680 --> 08:32.080
They were sending him home.

08:34.000 --> 08:36.160
He was the least unwell they said.

08:38.640 --> 08:41.320
Michael said, "Least unwell isn't well"

08:42.440 --> 08:43.720
and he agreed,

08:45.720 --> 08:48.640
but they needed his bed
for someone a lot worse than him.

08:50.280 --> 08:51.880
So he came home.

08:53.440 --> 08:55.840
And he got worse and worse.

08:59.560 --> 09:01.320
He asked me to phone Michael

09:02.000 --> 09:03.160
and I did.

09:04.000 --> 09:05.840
But Michael was asleep in bed.

09:07.800 --> 09:09.960
So I phoned the crisis team.

09:12.920 --> 09:15.200
If I hadn't done that,
he'd be alive today.

09:15.840 --> 09:20.040
The crisis team came,
Vernon had the chain on the door

09:20.120 --> 09:22.240
and he put the knife to his throat

09:22.320 --> 09:25.000
and he said he'd kill himself
before he let them in.

09:27.680 --> 09:29.720
So they phoned the police.

09:31.360 --> 09:33.320
Why they did that, I don't understand.

09:34.360 --> 09:37.040
When the police came and... [SOBS]

09:38.240 --> 09:40.400
-Where was he shot?
-There.

09:40.560 --> 09:44.680
No. Where in his body?

09:49.080 --> 09:50.320
In his heart.

09:52.040 --> 09:53.760
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

09:54.920 --> 09:55.960
I'll get it.

09:56.760 --> 09:57.960
[KNOCKING CONTINUES]

10:07.560 --> 10:08.840
What's going on?

10:08.960 --> 10:10.440
Just need a quick word
about those boys of yours.

10:11.520 --> 10:12.600
Yes?

10:12.720 --> 10:14.280
One of them pushed
the other against my door.

10:14.360 --> 10:16.720
And when I asked them to move,
they shouted abuse at me.

10:16.800 --> 10:19.600
-Abuse?
-Called me a queer to be precise.

10:20.360 --> 10:22.040
Now, look, I'm pushing 50,

10:22.120 --> 10:24.960
I can do without this kind of crap
on me own doorstep, yeah?

10:25.040 --> 10:26.480
You approached my sons?

10:26.600 --> 10:29.160
-I asked them to move, yes.
-Did you touch them?

10:29.240 --> 10:30.880
Of course I didn't.
What are you implying?

10:30.960 --> 10:33.400
Don't go anywhere near my sons again,
you hear me?

10:35.400 --> 10:37.760
Well, it's no wonder they carry on
like that if that's your attitude.

10:37.840 --> 10:40.520
What do you expect? They're children.

10:40.600 --> 10:42.920
-I expect an apology.
-No.

10:43.360 --> 10:45.640
For them to apologise
they'll have to talk to you

10:45.720 --> 10:48.560
and my children will have nothing
to do with the likes of you.

10:48.640 --> 10:50.320
-The likes of me?
-Yes.

10:50.400 --> 10:52.760
-What do you mean by that?
-You know exactly what I mean.

10:52.840 --> 10:54.400
I'm gay, is that what you're saying?

10:54.480 --> 10:55.680
I don't really recognise that word.

10:56.240 --> 10:58.640
I'm gay, therefore your boys
can call me queer.

10:59.400 --> 11:01.480
Fine, so next time
I see you in the street,

11:01.560 --> 11:03.360
I can call you a nigger, yeah?

11:03.440 --> 11:04.520
Bye.

11:05.680 --> 11:06.720
What did you just say?

11:07.760 --> 11:11.160
I said they call me queer,
I call you... [GRUNTS]

11:11.240 --> 11:12.280
Hey, Daniel!

11:12.840 --> 11:15.320
-What the hell's going on?
-Ask him.

11:16.680 --> 11:18.760
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

11:20.440 --> 11:21.480
Are you okay?

11:22.560 --> 11:23.840
What was all that about?

11:23.960 --> 11:25.480
-[GROANS]
-What did you say to him?

11:26.400 --> 11:28.160
Hey, are you all right?

11:28.960 --> 11:30.800
You need to put something on that.

11:31.240 --> 11:32.440
Some frozen peas...

11:32.520 --> 11:34.640
I don't need your advice,
thank you very much.

11:39.000 --> 11:40.280
Nothing to say for yourselves?

11:41.080 --> 11:43.360
I mean, what the hell
do you think you're playing at?

11:43.440 --> 11:45.240
Get upstairs and get out of my sight.

11:45.320 --> 11:46.680
I don't want to hear from you!

11:49.600 --> 11:50.760
What's going on?

11:52.080 --> 11:56.240
Nothing, Helen.
Come on, let's go inside...

12:01.480 --> 12:02.520
[SNIFFS]

12:07.240 --> 12:09.320
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

12:09.720 --> 12:12.080
[HISSES IN PAIN]

12:39.000 --> 12:40.680
[RADIO CHATTER]

12:42.920 --> 12:45.120
PC KNOX: Hello. Can we come in?

12:46.760 --> 12:47.880
Yeah.

12:53.920 --> 12:56.000
HELEN: He's coming home?
PC MAGEE: Sorry?

12:56.160 --> 12:58.280
Vernon. He's coming home?

12:58.360 --> 13:01.400
Mrs Oyenusi,
we're so sorry for your loss

13:01.480 --> 13:03.560
and we offer our heartfelt condolences.

13:03.640 --> 13:05.960
But we're not here about Vernon.

13:07.400 --> 13:09.040
So why are you here?

13:10.160 --> 13:13.080
-PC KNOX: Are you Mrs Oyenusi's brother?
-Yes.

13:13.960 --> 13:15.720
PC KNOX:
Could I take your name please, sir?

13:15.840 --> 13:17.680
Daniel. Daniel Martin.

13:18.120 --> 13:19.520
And how are you spelling that?

13:19.640 --> 13:22.000
M-A-R-T-I-N.

13:22.400 --> 13:23.480
Why?

13:23.840 --> 13:26.040
Mr Martin, we've received a complaint

13:26.120 --> 13:29.720
that you assaulted a man just outside
at roughly 2:15 this afternoon.

13:29.800 --> 13:32.440
-What are you talking about?
-DANIEL: Is this a joke?

13:32.520 --> 13:34.400
We wouldn't joke about something
as serious as this.

13:34.760 --> 13:36.000
Serious?

13:36.320 --> 13:39.200
PC KNOX: Sir, the man alleges
it was a homophobic attack.

13:39.480 --> 13:40.720
A hate crime.

13:40.960 --> 13:44.040
If found guilty of a hate crime,
you will go to prison, sir.

13:44.160 --> 13:46.400
Yes, sir. Very serious.

13:47.240 --> 13:48.600
DANIEL: More serious than the killing

13:48.680 --> 13:51.600
of a black teenager
by white police officers?

13:52.160 --> 13:53.880
See, I see
what you're doing here, officer.

13:54.400 --> 13:55.840
You've killed a young man

13:55.920 --> 13:59.320
therefore discredit him
and all his family, yeah? Hmm?

13:59.400 --> 14:01.800
-Did you assault Carl McKenna, sir?
-Carl?

14:02.440 --> 14:06.360
He came here hurling racist abuse,
but I did not assault him.

14:06.480 --> 14:08.040
Carl wouldn't do that.

14:08.640 --> 14:10.360
PC MAGEE:
He says you witnessed it, Father.

14:10.440 --> 14:12.200
It is Father, is it?

14:12.760 --> 14:14.000
Yeah, Michael will do.

14:15.440 --> 14:16.720
What did you see, Michael?

14:19.160 --> 14:20.840
I'll need some time to think about that.

14:20.960 --> 14:22.520
-PC MAGEE: Time?
-Yeah.

14:23.520 --> 14:26.920
It's a very simple thing, Michael.
Just tell us what you saw.

14:27.080 --> 14:28.480
-MICHAEL: Simple?
-Yeah.

14:28.680 --> 14:31.000
A lot of officers
witnessed Vernon's death,

14:31.080 --> 14:32.640
yet not one of them said what they saw.

14:32.760 --> 14:34.560
Why is that, if it is so simple?

14:40.960 --> 14:43.320
How long will you need
to think about it?

14:45.040 --> 14:46.800
I don't know, a day or two.

14:55.080 --> 14:56.160
[KNOCKING]

15:03.760 --> 15:04.840
MICHAEL: Hello, again.

15:07.000 --> 15:08.280
What do you want?

15:08.520 --> 15:11.200
Frozen peas. Put them on the pain.

15:11.600 --> 15:13.560
Wrap 'em in cloth first
or they'll stick to it.

15:15.040 --> 15:16.880
You've had direct experience, have you?

15:17.400 --> 15:18.440
Yeah.

15:18.720 --> 15:21.120
Before I was a priest
I was a professional gobshite

15:21.200 --> 15:23.720
and quite a few people
took a swing at me.

15:23.800 --> 15:24.880
[CHUCKLES]

15:26.800 --> 15:27.880
I'm Michael.

15:28.320 --> 15:29.400
Carl.

15:29.520 --> 15:31.920
-What can I do for you, Michael?
-Can I come in?

15:32.920 --> 15:34.040
It's not the Ritz.

15:34.120 --> 15:35.480
Oh, I don't mind.

15:37.880 --> 15:39.520
[TV MUSIC PLAYS FAINTLY]

15:42.360 --> 15:46.160
Quentin Crisp said after the third year
the dust doesn't get any worse.

15:47.480 --> 15:48.760
We live in hope.

15:50.320 --> 15:51.640
Oh... Listen.

15:52.360 --> 15:53.720
Get out, you, will you?

15:54.680 --> 15:55.960
-Sorry.
-[CHUCKLES]

15:56.280 --> 15:58.360
Have a seat, Father.
Let me turn that off.

15:58.440 --> 15:59.800
Ah, thanks.

15:59.960 --> 16:01.640
Would you like a drink?
A cup of tea, or...

16:01.720 --> 16:04.160
No, no, no, I'm fine. Thank you.

16:04.840 --> 16:06.400
[GROANS]

16:18.560 --> 16:19.760
CARL: Brenda.

16:20.600 --> 16:21.800
My mum.

16:26.640 --> 16:27.840
Forgive me, Father, it's the only thing

16:27.920 --> 16:30.960
that stops me poor little nerves
from jangling since she passed.

16:31.400 --> 16:33.160
[BREATHES SHAKILY]

16:34.280 --> 16:36.840
I'm not ready to let go
of her just yet, you know.

16:38.360 --> 16:40.480
Yeah, some people
never scatter the ashes.

16:40.880 --> 16:42.920
Others find it helps them let go.

16:43.360 --> 16:44.440
I smoked some.

16:46.440 --> 16:47.560
Sorry?

16:47.640 --> 16:51.440
When they first came back,
I sprinkled a tiny bit into a spliff.

16:52.840 --> 16:54.800
I was beside myself,

16:54.880 --> 16:57.200
hoped it would make her
a part of me forever, you know.

16:58.240 --> 17:01.200
But I've since read
very little of the body remains,

17:01.280 --> 17:04.280
so the only thing I got inside me
was oak veneer.

17:06.720 --> 17:07.760
Huh.

17:08.120 --> 17:09.840
It'll be three months on Thursday.

17:15.000 --> 17:16.480
The dreaded "c" word.

17:17.600 --> 17:20.640
I never knew it was possible
to miss someone so much.

17:20.800 --> 17:23.600
I'm 49 years of age,
I've never left home.

17:24.240 --> 17:25.880
We did everything together.

17:29.000 --> 17:30.040
[LIGHTER CLICKS]

17:33.040 --> 17:34.120
[COUGHS]

17:37.360 --> 17:38.520
What do you want?

17:41.040 --> 17:43.120
I want to talk to you
about this afternoon.

17:47.600 --> 17:48.680
Why?

17:48.800 --> 17:51.000
Well, I want to hear
your side of the story.

17:55.640 --> 17:57.720
I'm going to have to go to the shops.

17:58.200 --> 18:00.240
I'll tell it to you on the way, okay?

18:08.640 --> 18:09.960
CARL: I love it here.

18:10.400 --> 18:11.880
I cut through most days.

18:23.440 --> 18:25.360
Just look at that stonework.

18:26.040 --> 18:27.560
It's sublime, isn't it?

18:30.840 --> 18:32.320
Catacomb.

18:34.240 --> 18:35.720
Catacomb.

18:38.800 --> 18:42.000
Did you ever hear such a terrifying word
in your entire life?

18:43.360 --> 18:44.720
Catacomb.

18:53.920 --> 18:56.880
I first saw him
getting out of a cab outside Helen's.

18:58.560 --> 19:02.200
I approached him and asked him
to pass on some flowers to her,

19:02.280 --> 19:03.480
but he refused.

19:04.240 --> 19:06.920
He didn't give an explanation.
He didn't have to.

19:07.560 --> 19:11.520
Homophobia can be very subtle like that,
you know. You just know.

19:12.720 --> 19:16.120
Then a few hours later his boys were
messing about outside me door

19:16.200 --> 19:18.720
and one of them
pushed the other against it.

19:19.000 --> 19:23.240
So I went out and asked them, politely,
to move further down the street.

19:25.280 --> 19:28.280
They called me a queer
and ran off, laughing.

19:30.560 --> 19:33.360
So I knocked at Helen's,
and I told him what happened.

19:34.120 --> 19:36.800
Now, instead of reprimanding them

19:37.480 --> 19:40.760
he warned me never
to approach his children again,

19:40.840 --> 19:42.720
like I'm some kind of a...

19:42.880 --> 19:44.520
-Hmm.
-You know.

19:46.320 --> 19:48.440
When I realised
there was no apology forthcoming,

19:48.520 --> 19:49.720
I couldn't help myself.

19:49.800 --> 19:51.120
I turned around to him and I told him

19:51.200 --> 19:54.040
I said, "Yeah, maybe
when I see you walking down the street,

19:54.120 --> 19:57.520
"I might feel compelled to call you by
a certain name and see how you like it."

19:57.600 --> 19:59.440
-Yeah.
-[SIGHS]

20:01.960 --> 20:06.200
It was at that point you entered
stage left for the dramatic finale.

20:09.480 --> 20:12.960
Look, there's never
any justification for violence,

20:13.600 --> 20:16.240
but that family,
they've already suffered so much.

20:16.880 --> 20:18.960
CARL: You don't have to tell me, Father.

20:19.040 --> 20:23.000
What those bastards, excuse my French,
did to poor Vernon...

20:24.360 --> 20:26.760
[SIGHS] That was unforgivable.

20:28.120 --> 20:29.480
He was a good lad.

20:30.200 --> 20:32.320
He always gave me the time of day.

20:32.880 --> 20:35.400
Look, I'm not trying
to make excuses for him,

20:35.480 --> 20:37.920
but he'd just arrived
on a very long flight

20:38.000 --> 20:41.760
from a totally different culture.
He was jet-lagged, grieving...

20:43.280 --> 20:46.920
I'm grieving, I don't go around punching
innocent people in the face.

20:49.240 --> 20:50.440
Entrez.

20:51.920 --> 20:53.320
What are you doing?

20:54.160 --> 20:56.120
Sorry, Father, but I'm gaggin'.

20:57.280 --> 20:58.520
Me nerves...

21:01.720 --> 21:04.240
I don't really think
you should be doing that here.

21:04.800 --> 21:07.400
What else do you think
phone boxes are for these days?

21:07.800 --> 21:11.120
Oh, someone's been on the beak here.

21:13.160 --> 21:14.400
Cocaine.

21:19.520 --> 21:20.920
So, what made you become a priest?

21:21.320 --> 21:22.360
Hmm.

21:22.760 --> 21:25.200
Oh, please tell me it was
sunbeams through the window,

21:25.760 --> 21:29.600
bathing iridescent light,
the sound of heavenly choirs...

21:29.680 --> 21:32.080
[CHUCKLES]
If only it had been that obvious.

21:32.440 --> 21:35.000
Oh, don't mind me,
I watch too many films.

21:37.880 --> 21:39.760
-Are you celibate?
-Yes.

21:41.520 --> 21:44.920
I am too,
but not by choice, I can tell you.

21:47.560 --> 21:49.120
Are you allowed to have a wank?

21:51.240 --> 21:52.280
[LAUGHING]

21:52.360 --> 21:54.520
I'm sorry, I shouldn't have asked.

21:54.600 --> 21:57.760
I've often wondered, but I never
had the chance to ask until now.

21:57.880 --> 22:00.160
Let's face it,
it's not every day you find yourself

22:00.240 --> 22:03.640
skinning up with a catholic priest
in a public phone box now, is it?

22:08.120 --> 22:09.440
The... The church teaches

22:09.520 --> 22:12.720
that any sexual activity
outside marriage is wrong.

22:15.080 --> 22:16.800
I'll take that as a yes, then, shall I?

22:19.400 --> 22:20.440
[LIGHTER CLICKS]

22:44.000 --> 22:45.480
Oh, mind the cat, now.

22:47.160 --> 22:48.920
The cat never took a liking to me.

22:50.160 --> 22:52.840
The only reason I look after the bastard
is for Brenda.

22:57.840 --> 23:00.160
Thanks very much, I enjoyed that.

23:00.600 --> 23:01.680
Yeah.

23:02.920 --> 23:04.480
[WATER RUNNING]

23:04.560 --> 23:06.080
Do you sleep down here?

23:06.160 --> 23:07.280
Hmm?

23:07.400 --> 23:09.200
MICHAEL: I said,
"Do you sleep down here?"

23:09.600 --> 23:11.240
I don't really like going upstairs

23:11.320 --> 23:13.440
-since Brenda passed.
-Ah.

23:13.520 --> 23:16.040
Besides, it's freezing up there
and I've got no gas.

23:17.360 --> 23:18.560
How do you mean?

23:19.360 --> 23:22.560
Oh, they've got me on one of these
pre-paid-metre-things, you know.

23:22.880 --> 23:24.600
But it's not worth
putting anything on it.

23:24.760 --> 23:26.000
Why not?

23:26.240 --> 23:27.720
'Cause I owe them a fortune.

23:28.200 --> 23:29.560
So, if I put a tenner on the key

23:29.640 --> 23:31.200
they take most of it back straight away

23:31.280 --> 23:33.760
and then shit's run out again
before you know it.

23:34.200 --> 23:35.560
But it's been perishing.

23:36.400 --> 23:38.760
Well, you wouldn't believe the heat
that little beauty gives out.

23:40.960 --> 23:43.440
So how... How do you do your cooking?

23:43.560 --> 23:44.720
I don't.

23:46.440 --> 23:48.840
Well, look, I can't do
anything about your gas,

23:48.920 --> 23:52.120
but I can arrange vouchers
for the food bank

23:52.200 --> 23:53.840
if you ever felt that you needed...

23:53.920 --> 23:55.200
What?

23:56.200 --> 23:58.960
You think I don't know
what this is really about?

24:01.920 --> 24:04.840
You want me to forget everything,
don't you?

24:05.320 --> 24:06.400
Yeah.

24:07.600 --> 24:09.600
-Helen's going through hell right now.
-Right now.

24:09.680 --> 24:11.560
-This is the last thing she needs.
-I know.

24:11.640 --> 24:12.920
He's come over to ease her grief,

24:13.000 --> 24:14.160
-but he's adding to it.
-I know.

24:14.240 --> 24:16.720
I'm more than happy
to forget everything, Michael.

24:18.600 --> 24:21.240
Well thank you, Carl, thank you.
I appreciate that.

24:21.320 --> 24:24.400
The moment he comes over here
and shakes my hand,

24:24.480 --> 24:26.080
it's all forgotten.

24:27.800 --> 24:29.120
[SIGHS]

24:33.120 --> 24:34.720
All right, thanks.

24:47.000 --> 24:49.080
DANIEL: Shake his hand?

24:50.960 --> 24:54.400
Father, I'm disappointed that
you would even suggest such a thing.

24:54.520 --> 24:57.880
-Well, I just think for the sake of...
-Have you forgotten what he called me?

24:57.960 --> 25:02.360
Daniel, would it be so hard
to swallow your pride just this once?

25:02.440 --> 25:05.400
DANIEL: Helen, this isn't about pride.
This is about what is right.

25:05.480 --> 25:07.240
I'm sure if you actually spoke to Carl,

25:07.320 --> 25:09.640
you'd be able to find
some common ground.

25:09.720 --> 25:11.120
He's grieving, too.

25:11.200 --> 25:13.760
He only lost his mother
a few months back.

25:13.840 --> 25:17.960
Are you seriously comparing his grief
to what we are going through?

25:18.040 --> 25:20.160
No, no, of course not,
I'm just saying...

25:20.240 --> 25:22.200
-[EXHALES] Father...
-I mean...

25:22.280 --> 25:25.560
-My sister has lost her only son.
-MICHAEL: Yes.

25:25.640 --> 25:27.440
I have lost my nephew,

25:27.520 --> 25:31.080
and the only thing we care about
right now is bringing Vernon home.

25:31.160 --> 25:33.840
Everything else is totally irrelevant.

25:33.920 --> 25:37.320
So, as far as I am concerned,
that man can go to hell.

25:46.800 --> 25:48.200
[DISTANT HONKING]

25:53.480 --> 25:54.720
-[STRIKES]
-Oh! [LAUGHING]

25:54.800 --> 25:56.120
He's got a strike!

25:56.200 --> 25:59.080
"Is he gonna snatch victory
after the jaws of defeat?"

25:59.160 --> 26:00.360
It helps to go halfway down the alley,

26:00.440 --> 26:01.480
-doesn't it?
-Go away.

26:01.560 --> 26:02.960
Any closer,
he could have pushed 'em over.

26:03.040 --> 26:05.040
Hey, hey. Me foot...
Me foot was behind that line.

26:05.120 --> 26:06.360
-Were it, shite?
-It were!

26:06.440 --> 26:08.080
What do we do if it's a foul throw?

26:08.160 --> 26:09.520
-MAN: Were it a foul?
-Yes!

26:09.600 --> 26:12.240
-No, it was not, it was not.
-He's cheated.

26:12.320 --> 26:14.560
"Hey, you have to
feel sorry for his opponents,

26:14.640 --> 26:17.560
"up against the man, up against a man

26:17.640 --> 26:20.440
-"at the peak of his power."
-[CHATTERING]

26:20.520 --> 26:22.800
We'll never hear the last of this, now.

26:22.880 --> 26:25.160
"There's people on the pitch."

26:25.240 --> 26:26.960
-We're watching your feet.
-Yeah.

26:27.040 --> 26:29.120
"They think it's all over..."

26:29.200 --> 26:30.760
Over line, it's a foul.

26:31.320 --> 26:32.520
MEN: Oh, no.

26:32.600 --> 26:33.640
[ALL GROAN]

26:33.720 --> 26:34.880
"It is now!"

26:35.160 --> 26:36.480
[LAUGHING]

26:36.560 --> 26:37.800
-Ooh!
-Bloody hell!

26:37.880 --> 26:39.000
I can't believe it!

26:39.080 --> 26:40.520
-How did you do that?
-Can you believe that?

26:49.440 --> 26:50.880
[SIGHS]

26:57.000 --> 26:59.520
"Behold the lamb of God.

26:59.600 --> 27:03.120
"Behold him who takes away
the sins of the world.

27:04.560 --> 27:08.040
"Blessed are those
called to the supper of the lamb."

27:09.280 --> 27:11.800
BOTH: Lord, I am not worthy...

27:12.480 --> 27:15.760
"that you should enter under my roof,

27:16.560 --> 27:22.000
"but only say the word
and my soul shall be healed.

27:27.280 --> 27:28.360
[BREAKS SACRAMENTAL BREAD]

27:34.320 --> 27:35.640
Mum...

27:39.240 --> 27:40.560
The body of Christ.

27:41.360 --> 27:42.760
Amen.

27:49.520 --> 27:51.000
[MICHAEL EXHALES]

27:56.160 --> 27:57.200
[GULPS]

28:01.120 --> 28:02.880
The blood of Christ.

28:03.760 --> 28:05.120
[WEAKLY] Amen.

28:15.440 --> 28:17.200
[SOBBING]

28:27.960 --> 28:29.960
[SOBS]

28:32.200 --> 28:33.440
[KISSES]

28:39.560 --> 28:41.080
Oh, Mum.

28:42.480 --> 28:44.520
[BOTH SOBBING]

28:48.840 --> 28:50.440
Oh, Mum!

28:52.560 --> 28:54.960
[BOTH SOBBING AND WHISPERING]

29:01.040 --> 29:02.440
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

29:02.600 --> 29:06.240
MRS DEVANEY: Open that door!
I know you're in there!

29:06.320 --> 29:07.520
Come on, open the door!

29:07.600 --> 29:10.720
I can't be standing on this doorstep
all day and night!

29:10.880 --> 29:12.200
Come on!

29:12.320 --> 29:14.520
Open up! I want my money!

29:14.600 --> 29:16.560
I saw him go in there!

29:17.960 --> 29:19.200
-[KNOCKING CONTINUES]
-Come on!

29:19.280 --> 29:21.160
[TRAIN WHISTLE BLOWING]

29:41.760 --> 29:43.120
Oh, hello.

29:44.880 --> 29:47.120
Do you want to come through?

30:00.600 --> 30:01.680
You're not used to this?

30:04.080 --> 30:05.800
It's how it is these days.

30:07.240 --> 30:10.200
I could turn the chair around,
face that way.

30:11.480 --> 30:13.880
We could go elsewhere,
somewhere traditional.

30:13.960 --> 30:15.080
Please.

30:20.360 --> 30:22.240
Right. Follow me.

30:34.680 --> 30:37.320
Uh, you go in there. I go in here.

30:44.600 --> 30:45.640
Is that better?

30:46.520 --> 30:48.480
Yes, thank you.

30:51.080 --> 30:53.720
I confess to Almighty God,

30:53.800 --> 30:56.280
to blessed Mary, ever virgin,

30:56.360 --> 30:58.920
to blessed Michael the archangel,

30:59.000 --> 31:01.640
to the holy apostles Peter and Paul...

31:01.720 --> 31:04.920
[INHALES] To all the saints
and to you, my father,

31:05.000 --> 31:09.240
that I have sinned exceedingly
in thought, word and deed.

31:09.360 --> 31:11.000
Through my fault.

31:11.080 --> 31:12.440
Through my fault.

31:12.520 --> 31:14.760
Through my most grievous fault.

31:21.920 --> 31:23.120
Father?

31:26.480 --> 31:30.000
May God help you to confess
your sins with true sorrow.

31:34.920 --> 31:39.600
I have examined my conscience, father,
and punching that man is not on it.

31:40.120 --> 31:42.480
I did it in righteous anger,

31:42.560 --> 31:46.400
the same anger that made Christ
drive the money men from the temple.

31:47.200 --> 31:49.560
When a white man
calls a black man a nigger,

31:49.640 --> 31:51.640
he must be punished.

31:51.720 --> 31:53.440
He only used that word

31:53.520 --> 31:55.320
because your boys had called him queer

31:55.400 --> 31:56.800
and you refused to do anything about it.

31:56.880 --> 31:59.720
Those words are nowhere near equivalent.

31:59.800 --> 32:02.000
You can hide your sexuality,
I can't hide this.

32:02.640 --> 32:05.200
You really believe Carl McKenna
could hide the kind of man he is?

32:05.320 --> 32:07.800
Yes, but he chooses not to.

32:08.160 --> 32:10.760
In fact, he goes further,
he advertises it.

32:10.840 --> 32:14.680
And, in doing that, he is a danger
to my sons, to all our sons.

32:14.760 --> 32:15.800
Why?

32:15.880 --> 32:17.840
Because homosexual boys
get bullied, Father.

32:17.920 --> 32:19.280
As do heterosexual.

32:19.360 --> 32:21.840
Much more homosexual than heterosexual.

32:21.920 --> 32:25.440
-Their lives are made a misery.
-Yes. In which case...

32:25.520 --> 32:27.080
we should all try to be more tolerant.

32:27.160 --> 32:29.200
Teenage boys are not tolerant, Father,

32:29.280 --> 32:31.080
they're vicious.

32:31.160 --> 32:32.600
They turn on you if you stammer.

32:32.680 --> 32:34.720
If you limp, if you lisp.

32:34.800 --> 32:38.520
But show them you're homosexual
and they turn on you quickest of all.

32:40.000 --> 32:41.400
You call them gay in this country.

32:41.480 --> 32:43.760
[SCOFFS] They're not gay.

32:43.840 --> 32:45.520
They are sad.

32:45.600 --> 32:47.080
So, so sad.

32:47.200 --> 32:49.760
And I will make sure
that my boys know that.

32:49.840 --> 32:53.920
Better to live a lie
than reveal a truth like that.

32:54.760 --> 32:57.080
You say your anger is "righteous"?

32:57.160 --> 32:58.880
-Yes.
-In the eyes of God, I assume.

32:59.320 --> 33:01.680
-Yeah.
-But not in the eyes of the law.

33:01.960 --> 33:04.440
In the eyes of the law,
you have committed a serious crime

33:04.520 --> 33:07.480
-and you will go to prison for it.
-Yes.

33:07.560 --> 33:08.880
-Unless...
-Yes?

33:10.720 --> 33:12.640
You apologise. Shake hands.

33:13.680 --> 33:15.840
That would be utterly insincere.

33:15.920 --> 33:17.360
Nevertheless.

33:19.080 --> 33:20.640
[DANIEL SIGHS]

33:22.520 --> 33:24.000
You can resolve this, Father.

33:25.920 --> 33:27.400
How?

33:27.480 --> 33:29.960
You did not see me strike that man.

33:35.360 --> 33:36.640
You want me to lie to the police?

33:36.720 --> 33:37.960
Have they not lied to us?

33:38.040 --> 33:40.640
To expose myself to Carl McKenna
as a liar,

33:40.720 --> 33:43.000
and then say mass,
give out the Holy Sacrament?

33:43.080 --> 33:44.960
You're asking me to do that?

33:45.120 --> 33:47.720
It's no worse than
what you're asking of me.

33:49.440 --> 33:51.520
To say I'm sorry when I am not.

33:51.600 --> 33:54.400
To go against my faith, my Catholicism.

33:54.520 --> 33:56.160
And for what?

33:56.240 --> 33:57.880
Fear of imprisonment.

33:59.120 --> 34:01.240
[SCOFFS] That is cowardice.

34:01.320 --> 34:02.720
That is hypocrisy.

34:02.800 --> 34:05.400
I will not do it,

34:05.480 --> 34:08.680
and I am disgusted that
a catholic priest should ask me to.

34:16.800 --> 34:18.200
[FIRE ALARM BEEPING]

34:22.360 --> 34:23.360
[SIGHS]

34:24.880 --> 34:26.280
[BEEPING CONTINUES]

34:44.600 --> 34:46.280
I'm not doing it.

34:47.280 --> 34:49.480
"I'm not your skivvy," Mum said.

35:00.760 --> 35:02.440
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

35:02.560 --> 35:04.880
POLICEWOMAN: [MUFFLED] Father Kerrigan.

35:05.680 --> 35:08.160
[KNOCKING CONTINUES]

35:10.400 --> 35:12.120
Are you in there, sir?

35:14.040 --> 35:16.040
-[CHUCKLING]
-[MOBILE RINGING]

35:16.840 --> 35:18.520
What's he doing to you?

35:19.200 --> 35:22.160
-Hello.
-Hi, Andrew, it's Michael Kerrigan.

35:22.280 --> 35:24.600
-I need some advice.
-Right.

35:25.040 --> 35:26.920
There's two coppers outside.

35:27.000 --> 35:28.840
-Yeah, I know.
-You know?

35:29.560 --> 35:30.560
Yeah.

35:31.080 --> 35:32.800
Have they come to take me in
to make a statement?

35:34.200 --> 35:35.280
Yeah.

35:35.360 --> 35:37.040
Have I got to make that statement?

35:37.120 --> 35:38.760
Well, no.
Hang on.

35:40.080 --> 35:41.160
No. You don't have to.

35:41.800 --> 35:44.920
Well, if I make that statement and
Daniel's found guilty, what will he get?

35:45.680 --> 35:47.360
I'd say four to six years.

35:47.440 --> 35:49.680
It's a hate crime, you see.

35:49.760 --> 35:51.520
But when he's done it, Michael,
he'll be thrown out the country

35:51.600 --> 35:53.640
and won't be allowed back in.

35:54.280 --> 35:56.200
Which means he'll never see Helen again.

35:56.280 --> 35:58.440
It's horrible, isn't it?

35:58.520 --> 36:00.920
Seeing other people suffer
for your principles?

36:03.520 --> 36:05.520
I know that I couldn't do it.

36:07.600 --> 36:08.720
Thanks.

36:08.800 --> 36:10.240
You're welcome.

36:12.200 --> 36:13.600
[DOG BARKING]

36:29.400 --> 36:32.560
Look, Carl, you've got to remember
that in his country

36:32.640 --> 36:33.960
it's still illegal to be gay.

36:34.120 --> 36:36.640
You can make all the excuses you want,

36:36.720 --> 36:39.160
but this has got nothing to do
with the colour of his skin

36:39.240 --> 36:40.680
or what country he's from.

36:40.760 --> 36:43.520
This is about religion and nothing else.

36:43.600 --> 36:47.320
Now, every morning I look out of
me window and I see tiny little kids

36:47.400 --> 36:50.880
heading off to that school of yours,
and guess what? Yeah...

36:50.960 --> 36:53.680
They'll also be taught
that being gay is a sin.

36:53.760 --> 36:57.000
That it's perfectly acceptable
to treat people like me with contempt.

36:57.320 --> 37:02.400
It's a cycle of hatred perpetuated
by your church, and I'll tell you what.

37:03.480 --> 37:06.640
As far as I'm concerned,
the world would be a better place

37:06.720 --> 37:09.240
when Catholicism and every other
goddamned religion

37:09.320 --> 37:10.880
has been consigned to history.

37:10.960 --> 37:13.360
My church teaches compassion
for all human beings

37:13.440 --> 37:16.920
regardless of religion,
race, sexuality.

37:17.000 --> 37:19.200
And it also teaches that I'm a sinner.

37:19.280 --> 37:21.280
Which is something that you
go along with, Michael,

37:21.360 --> 37:24.360
'cause if you didn't, yeah,
you'd be on the dole.

37:24.480 --> 37:28.400
Look, I'm not asking you
to do this for me, or for him,

37:28.480 --> 37:31.400
I'm asking you to do it for Helen,
she's suffered enough, Carl.

37:31.480 --> 37:33.760
And if you had any idea
how much I'd suffered,

37:33.840 --> 37:37.000
you wouldn't dream of putting me
in this position.

37:37.080 --> 37:41.080
Now, the police told me that if anyone
tries to intimidate me

37:41.160 --> 37:43.360
or put pressure on me
to drop the charges

37:43.440 --> 37:45.120
that I am to report them immediately.

37:45.200 --> 37:46.840
Well, I'm not trying
to put pressure on you.

37:47.840 --> 37:49.480
Have you made your statement yet?

37:51.000 --> 37:52.440
-Have you?
-[SIGHS]

37:54.600 --> 37:56.760
And you make out that you're impartial?

37:56.840 --> 37:58.720
Just go, Father.

37:58.800 --> 38:00.920
I think we both know whose side
you're really on.

38:01.000 --> 38:03.520
Believe me, Carl, I'm on no-one's side.

38:03.600 --> 38:07.040
I'm like the man with the chip
on both shoulders.

38:07.120 --> 38:10.000
I'm just as screwed up
about straight sex as I am gay.

38:10.600 --> 38:13.960
I will make a statement, yeah,
and I'll tell the absolute truth,

38:14.040 --> 38:16.560
but, right now,
there's nothing I'd like more

38:16.640 --> 38:18.840
than to get the four of us together
in a room

38:18.920 --> 38:20.920
because I'm sick of
this Ban Ki-moon act.

38:22.680 --> 38:24.720
Oh, please, tell me you're joking?

38:24.800 --> 38:25.880
Look!

38:25.960 --> 38:28.200
If not for me, then for Helen.

38:36.520 --> 38:38.160
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

38:38.240 --> 38:41.160
This is to remind us
of the presence of Christ...

38:42.960 --> 38:46.600
...and to enable us to speak truth
with compassion.

38:55.640 --> 38:57.240
[EXHALES]

38:57.320 --> 39:01.760
All I've ever wanted is to set
a good example to my sons

39:03.120 --> 39:06.600
and protect them from the evils
of this world.

39:06.680 --> 39:11.560
And in here I know
that homosexuality is one of them.

39:12.520 --> 39:17.240
And not because
I'm homophobic or repulsed

39:17.320 --> 39:20.320
by what two men choose to do together.

39:20.400 --> 39:23.040
But in the Bible

39:23.120 --> 39:28.160
it clearly states that homosexuals
will not inherit the kingdom of God.

39:28.440 --> 39:30.760
I was raised a Catholic, too.

39:31.680 --> 39:35.000
I loved it,
believed it with all my heart.

39:37.600 --> 39:40.200
But I also knew that I was different.

39:42.520 --> 39:45.320
I even wondered if God
was calling me to be a priest.

39:46.120 --> 39:49.000
But I soon realised, no,
I was just gay.

39:49.640 --> 39:52.720
I prayed and prayed for God
to make it stop,

39:52.800 --> 39:54.920
to make me "normal",

39:55.760 --> 39:57.120
but he didn't listen.

39:58.320 --> 40:01.160
Now I'd been brought up to believe
that being gay was a sin,

40:01.240 --> 40:03.000
that God hated gay people.

40:04.160 --> 40:07.240
So why would I choose such a thing, hmm?

40:07.320 --> 40:10.520
Why would I choose such a thing
when I knew that it meant

40:10.600 --> 40:13.800
that the church that I loved
would no longer welcome me?

40:15.160 --> 40:17.640
Choose? [SCOFFS]
Don't make me laugh.

40:18.120 --> 40:20.600
This will hurt you both,

40:20.680 --> 40:23.760
but in these circumstances I cannot lie.

40:25.720 --> 40:29.040
Daniel, you've always been
holier than thou.

40:30.600 --> 40:35.000
Carl, you have always been one to light
the blue touchpaper and then run away.

40:35.680 --> 40:37.480
And now you have met.

40:38.160 --> 40:40.200
And it is a match made in hell.

40:41.560 --> 40:45.480
Two stupid, stubborn men
refusing to back down,

40:45.560 --> 40:50.080
locking horns, totally forgetting
the only thing that should matter.

40:51.440 --> 40:52.960
Bringing Vernon home.

40:53.320 --> 40:54.360
Yeah.

40:56.040 --> 41:00.480
The world is full of gay men
who can hide their sexuality,

41:00.560 --> 41:01.760
live a lie.

41:02.720 --> 41:05.920
But do you seriously believe that
that was ever an option for me?

41:06.320 --> 41:10.800
The way I am, the way I speak,
it's not some affectation,

41:10.880 --> 41:15.920
it's not some show, it's not trying
to shock or intimidate anyone,

41:16.000 --> 41:20.520
it's just the way I was born,
and I make no apology for that.

41:20.600 --> 41:22.440
At least, not anymore, I don't.

41:22.520 --> 41:24.560
And if you believe in God

41:24.640 --> 41:28.640
then you also have to believe that
it was your God who created me this way.

41:28.840 --> 41:30.680
You were in pain, Carl.

41:31.720 --> 41:33.520
Angry,

41:33.600 --> 41:36.640
just waiting for someone to come along
for you to lash out,

41:36.720 --> 41:39.520
and you want to know how I know that?

41:39.680 --> 41:42.000
Because I feel exactly the same.

41:42.320 --> 41:44.640
I feel just as angry as you.

41:44.720 --> 41:47.280
I know what it feels like
when the person you love most of all

41:47.360 --> 41:49.560
in this world is taken from you.

41:51.280 --> 41:54.320
When your only reason to wake up
in the morning is no longer there.

41:54.560 --> 41:56.560
I wasn't even going to report it.

41:56.640 --> 41:59.000
I didn't think they'd take it seriously.

42:00.000 --> 42:01.400
But credit where credit is due.

42:01.480 --> 42:04.200
I was amazed how supportive they were.

42:04.280 --> 42:05.840
When I was growing up back in the '80s,

42:05.920 --> 42:08.720
gay bashing was virtually
the national sport

42:08.800 --> 42:11.280
and most people in this country
were gold medallists.

42:13.120 --> 42:16.800
But, now, finally, things are
starting to change...

42:16.880 --> 42:18.120
and hallelujah for that,

42:18.200 --> 42:20.920
because the only way to stamp out
this kind of hatred

42:21.000 --> 42:23.480
is to come down heavy
on those who perpetrate it.

42:23.760 --> 42:27.600
DANIEL: A sinner needs a priest, yes,

42:27.680 --> 42:30.840
but first let him be contrite,

42:30.920 --> 42:33.600
ashamed, penitent.

42:35.200 --> 42:36.960
This man is none of those things.

42:38.440 --> 42:43.240
His mincing, his voice, his innuendos
all announce

42:43.320 --> 42:45.920
that he is ready to sin again,

42:46.000 --> 42:49.600
that he is proud of it, boastful of it.

42:51.760 --> 42:54.600
This is a sin that my church
has utterly condemned

42:54.680 --> 42:57.120
so how can a priest find it so amusing?

42:59.800 --> 43:01.560
[SIGHS] Uh...

43:02.320 --> 43:04.840
I didn't intend to speak, er,

43:04.920 --> 43:07.440
but I suppose I should answer that, yes?

43:07.520 --> 43:08.600
Yes.

43:08.960 --> 43:11.480
I am not amused by it,
I am amused by him.

43:12.200 --> 43:14.040
DANIEL: Really?
MICHAEL: Yeah.

43:15.640 --> 43:17.920
I suppose we were all teenagers, once.

43:18.000 --> 43:21.320
-Yeah.
-Confused at times about our sexuality.

43:23.120 --> 43:24.200
Yeah.

43:24.280 --> 43:29.800
So how did you feel, Father, when
you thought you might be a homosexual?

43:36.280 --> 43:39.680
The candle is still burning,
Christ is still here,

43:39.760 --> 43:41.800
encouraging us to speak truth.

43:43.120 --> 43:48.280
How did you feel when you thought
you might be homosexual?

43:52.120 --> 43:53.640
It was the 1970s...

43:53.720 --> 43:56.000
How did you feel?

44:02.400 --> 44:03.440
Erm...

44:04.400 --> 44:05.880
Suicidal.

44:07.760 --> 44:08.840
Thank you.

44:18.760 --> 44:20.040
CARL: Er...

44:20.880 --> 44:23.160
Enough of this small talk.

44:29.960 --> 44:31.120
Thank you, Father.

44:38.200 --> 44:39.880
HELEN: Bye, Michael.

