47:22.960 --> 47:24.240
Daniel won't either.

47:24.320 --> 47:25.560
I know what I should say,

47:25.640 --> 47:29.440
"Daniel, thanks to Catholic teaching
you're a totally fucked-up human being

47:29.520 --> 47:31.600
"and that's okay, 'cause so was I.

47:31.680 --> 47:35.080
"Ignore everything the church says
on the subject of sex, Daniel.

47:35.160 --> 47:37.760
"I do that.
Every priest I know does that.

47:37.840 --> 47:40.960
"You can quote scripture till you're
blue in the face, papal pronouncements,

47:41.040 --> 47:43.840
"edicts, whatever,
they're all utter shite."

47:46.520 --> 47:48.400
Or words to that effect.

47:49.840 --> 47:51.520
Didn't you want sugar?

47:51.600 --> 47:53.320
-Yeah.
-[CHUCKLES]

47:54.400 --> 47:56.160
Good job I didn't take up smoking.

47:57.880 --> 47:59.720
Ah. I'm sorry to bring this one
on you, as well.

47:59.800 --> 48:02.000
-Nah, you're okay.
-I can cope usually, honest.

48:02.080 --> 48:03.680
You're fine, man.

48:05.240 --> 48:07.240
It's a bit like buses, isn't it?

48:07.320 --> 48:10.680
You wait all your life
for a decent dilemma to come along

48:11.720 --> 48:13.800
and then three arrive at the one time.

48:14.640 --> 48:15.960
What can I do?

48:16.040 --> 48:18.560
Well, we could pray to the lord.

48:18.640 --> 48:22.360
-He usually comes up with something.
-Not this time, Peter.

48:22.840 --> 48:24.880
Irresistible force meets
immovable object.

48:24.960 --> 48:26.160
I need a miracle.

48:29.960 --> 48:31.120
Hello.

48:33.120 --> 48:34.200
Yes?

48:36.960 --> 48:38.920
-Vernon can come home.
-No!

